The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, August 21, 2004 				 Pak breather for Divya
																								Peshawar, Aug. 20 (AFP): A Pakistani court has allowed Divya Dayanandan  rechristened Hafza Aman  to stay on in the country till the government reaches a decision on granting her citizenship.																								Divya, a 25-year-old doctor from Kerala, had married Pakistani citizen Aman Khan after meeting him in Ukraine where they were studying medicine. She recently gave birth to a boy.																								Divya had converted to Islam before marriage and applied for Pakistani citizenship in June. But the interior ministry turned it down.																								The Peshawar High Court has allowed Hafza to stay... till further orders and has asked the government to explain the reasons behind rejection of her application, her lawyer Osman Tarlandi said.
